WEBVTT

00:02.003 --> 00:04.714
(PEOPLE CLAMORING)

00:04.839 --> 00:08.343
Whoever thought walking in a circle at
two miles an hour would be draining?

00:08.468 --> 00:11.137
Fresh air, exercise.

00:11.262 --> 00:13.306
You know, some things
do have their negative sides.

00:13.431 --> 00:15.517
Our income just
got cut in half.

00:15.642 --> 00:18.061
And we get to spend
twice as much time together.

00:18.186 --> 00:20.647
More, if you don't leave
before your lunch hour is over.

00:20.772 --> 00:22.315
(CHUCKLES)

00:22.899 --> 00:24.818
Out of my way.

00:24.943 --> 00:27.612
We have a legal right
to hold you up for 15 seconds.

00:27.737 --> 00:29.072
Fifteen, fourteen...

00:29.197 --> 00:30.198
One.

00:30.323 --> 00:31.866
Eleven, ten...

00:32.784 --> 00:33.785
Ow!

00:35.537 --> 00:37.330
Just trying to do my job.

00:38.873 --> 00:42.127
Hey, relax.
Three more seconds and you can go.

00:44.921 --> 00:47.465
Are you telling
me what to do?

00:47.716 --> 00:49.300
It's okay.

00:50.343 --> 00:51.970
Just take a breath.

00:52.095 --> 00:54.055
Get the hell off me!

00:54.180 --> 00:56.558
(LAUGHS) I think
it's been 15...

01:00.687 --> 01:02.188
You Okay?

01:04.983 --> 01:05.859
(THUD)

01:06.151 --> 01:07.652
WOMAN: Oh, my God. Jeff?

01:39.225 --> 01:41.561
(ALL CHATTERING)

01:43.396 --> 01:44.439
WOMAN: Standby.

01:52.155 --> 01:53.156
(SLURPING)

01:56.034 --> 01:57.160
Place is a mess.

01:57.285 --> 02:00.079
Welcome to a world without nurses.
Here, you can start with these.

02:00.205 --> 02:02.457
HOUSE: It's not my fault.
I don't use nurses.

02:02.665 --> 02:04.459
Cuddy was looking for you,
said she would send you down here.

02:04.584 --> 02:06.377
I know. That's why I'm here.

02:06.503 --> 02:08.671
Because Cuddy
hasn't found you yet.

02:08.797 --> 02:12.842
She's going to look everywhere
except the place she wants me to be.

02:26.314 --> 02:28.358
- Hey.
- I've got an aortic dissection here.

02:28.483 --> 02:30.735
What's with the idiot?

02:30.860 --> 02:31.820
(CAMERON SIGHS)

02:32.737 --> 02:35.573
Fainting spell
and a recent history of dysgeusia,

02:35.698 --> 02:37.367
everything tastes like
lemon meringue pie.

02:37.492 --> 02:38.785
You want to take him?

02:38.910 --> 02:39.911
No.

02:43.915 --> 02:45.583
Si"

02:45.708 --> 02:48.294
Why do you have two
lunches in front of you?

02:48.419 --> 02:50.380
Been here for two meals.

02:50.755 --> 02:52.507
- And you're happy with that?
- No.

02:52.757 --> 02:54.926
I just don't see much
use in complaining.

02:55.301 --> 02:56.719
Seriously?

02:58.388 --> 03:00.014
It's a pretty useful tool.

03:00.223 --> 03:02.767
You complain,
make people miserable.

03:03.393 --> 03:05.728
Then they do what you want,
to make the misery go away.

03:05.854 --> 03:08.731
We probably should say something.
Maybe I can call one of the doctors...

03:08.857 --> 03:10.775
They're doing their best.

03:14.904 --> 03:15.905
Ow!

03:16.030 --> 03:17.699
What the hell?

03:18.783 --> 03:20.994
I'm sure it was an accident.

03:21.536 --> 03:23.121
Is he Canadian?

03:23.246 --> 03:24.998
He's a low priority.

03:25.665 --> 03:27.125
Is that a yes?

03:27.625 --> 03:30.461
- He's just...
- Happy-

03:31.045 --> 03:33.798
I've got to stop this,
before it spreads.

03:33.923 --> 03:34.883
(WHISTLES)

03:35.758 --> 03:37.135
You guys are done.

03:39.512 --> 03:43.349
Could be a metabolic disorder,
toxic exposure,

03:43.474 --> 03:46.853
carcinoma of the tongue metastasized
to the brain, epilepsy, M.S.

03:46.978 --> 03:50.148
Or it could be the flu
and we should all be back in the E.R.

03:50.273 --> 03:52.901
No, you're ignoring
the big symptom.

03:53.026 --> 03:57.530
What if we were looking at both the flu
and decent parenting.

03:58.448 --> 04:00.909
Okay, you two
are perfectly healthy.

04:01.034 --> 04:03.119
This guy wasn't pandering.
He wasn't vanilla nice.

04:03.244 --> 04:05.788
He was nice without any
aspiration of personal gain.

04:06.039 --> 04:07.665
I'm thinking genetic defect.

04:07.790 --> 04:09.959
(SCOFFS) Niceness
is a defect?

04:11.044 --> 04:14.797
Three cavemen see a stranger
running towards them with a spear

04:14.923 --> 04:19.010
one fights, one flees, one smiles
and invites him over for fondue.

04:19.135 --> 04:20.970
That last guy didn't last
long enough to procreate.

04:21.095 --> 04:23.932
And how long has the
patient been suffering?

04:24.057 --> 04:26.351
At least as long as his wife
has known him, eleven years.

04:26.476 --> 04:28.811
The chances of him having an undiagnosed
pathology for that long...

04:28.937 --> 04:30.146
What are you saying?

04:30.271 --> 04:31.481
Evolution is wrong?

04:31.606 --> 04:35.109
(SCOFFS) Where do you think
we are? 21st century America?

04:35.234 --> 04:37.695
He's saying that
statistics are true, too.

04:37.820 --> 04:39.364
The world is a bell curve,

04:39.489 --> 04:41.699
most of us fall within
the standard deviation.

04:41.824 --> 04:43.034
But there are outliers.

04:43.159 --> 04:46.454
And if we believe in the existence
of extreme jerkiness,

04:46.579 --> 04:49.290
which I suspect that we do,

04:51.084 --> 04:54.170
then we also have to accept the
existence of the opposite extreme.

04:54.295 --> 04:57.632
You want it to be a symptom,
because then we're supposed to be jerks,

04:57.757 --> 05:00.051
which means you don't even
have to try to be nice.

05:01.427 --> 05:04.222
Okay, maybe I am biased.
Let's take a vote.

05:04.347 --> 05:06.891
Who thinks that niceness
is not a symptom?

05:07.976 --> 05:11.562
And who thinks that
their vote counts?

05:16.234 --> 05:19.195
You two, check out his home
for toxins. Taub and 31...

05:19.320 --> 05:20.363
31?

05:21.197 --> 05:23.950
Oh, I'm sorry, I thought that
either way was good with you.

05:24.450 --> 05:28.287
Taub and Thirteen, MRI for tumors,
EEG for nerve damage

05:28.413 --> 05:31.207
and test whatever comes out of him
for everything else.

05:44.554 --> 05:46.514
CHASE: Too much axis tilt.

05:47.390 --> 05:51.352
Don't release until your thumb's
at the bottom of the ball.

05:51.769 --> 05:53.438
I assume Wilson was busy.

05:53.563 --> 05:54.981
Again.

06:08.036 --> 06:09.996
No axis tilt.

06:14.042 --> 06:15.334
With Amber?

06:15.460 --> 06:16.419
Again.

06:16.753 --> 06:20.048
Still. It was nice of you
to invite me. This is fun.

06:22.050 --> 06:24.302
No, it wasn't.
No, it isn't.

06:24.427 --> 06:26.137
I didn't invite you to
be nice, I invited you

06:26.262 --> 06:30.099
because bowling isn't one of the two
things guys do by themselves.

06:30.558 --> 06:31.851
What's the second thing?

06:32.185 --> 06:34.020
Other hand.

06:38.024 --> 06:41.486
Well, if people are incapable of being
nice, why bother having the word?

06:42.278 --> 06:44.072
The ontological
proof of niceness.

06:44.197 --> 06:47.450
The existence of the word proves the
existence of the concept.

06:47.575 --> 06:50.536
Look out for those minotaurs
on your drive home.

06:50.870 --> 06:54.707
And I thought motives didn't matter,
only results mattered.

06:55.541 --> 06:57.126
So what are you gonna do?

06:57.460 --> 06:59.796
To screw up Wilson's relationship
so you don't have to listen to me

06:59.921 --> 07:01.464
while you bowl.

07:01.714 --> 07:06.594
I wish the best for them,
and their tragically deformed children.

07:07.929 --> 07:10.306
She's good at being bad.

07:10.431 --> 07:11.390
(GUTTER BALLING)

07:11.599 --> 07:13.226
You might not be
able to destroy her.

07:13.351 --> 07:17.105
As long as I give it my best shot,
I can hold my head high.

07:17.230 --> 07:19.941
Cameron had this
one insufferable friend.

07:20.066 --> 07:23.236
She wasn't going to get rid of her,
and I sure wasn't going to join them.

07:23.361 --> 07:26.405
So I just said,
"See her on Thursdays."

07:26.531 --> 07:29.200
I know it's not as exciting
as an exploding birthday cake,

07:29.325 --> 07:33.871
but, hell, I don't want to hang out
with her every night anyway.

07:33.996 --> 07:38.334
That's amazing. Cameron only has
one insufferable friend?

07:55.726 --> 07:57.812
Joint custody.

07:57.937 --> 07:59.355
Of Wilson?

07:59.480 --> 08:01.858
Unless we have
another love child.

08:02.483 --> 08:03.693
Deal with him.

08:03.943 --> 08:05.820
He needs a mother figure.

08:06.070 --> 08:07.864
I'm not saying you're not entitled
to spend time with him.

08:08.114 --> 08:10.116
I'm just saying
I'm entitled, too.

08:11.033 --> 08:14.245
I don't know how to deal with him
when he's being reasonable.

08:14.370 --> 08:16.706
This is reasonable?
This is crazy.

08:16.831 --> 08:18.958
You're not a child,
you can make your own plans.

08:19.083 --> 08:22.128
No. Crazy is what House
would normally do in this situation,

08:22.253 --> 08:24.297
swap your lubricant
with super glue.

08:24.422 --> 08:25.464
The man knows me.

08:25.590 --> 08:29.051
This is his way
of accepting us.

08:29.177 --> 08:30.887
It's actually a very
touching moment.

08:31.012 --> 08:35.016
I'm proposing I get every other
day and every other weekend.

08:39.187 --> 08:41.272
I have Yoga Wednesdays,
you can have him then,

08:41.397 --> 08:44.108
but you have to have
him home by 11:00.

08:46.068 --> 08:48.571
We can swap weekends.

08:48.696 --> 08:50.865
Mondays and Wednesdays.
And midnight.

08:50.990 --> 08:53.659
If he's not home till midnight,
we won't be asleep till almost 2:00.

08:53.784 --> 08:56.078
Wilson, make a ruling.

08:56.204 --> 08:57.663
(LAUGHS)

08:57.788 --> 08:58.956
No.

08:59.081 --> 09:02.210
You two are like dogs circling
each other in the park.

09:02.335 --> 09:05.171
And I say that
with all the love in the world.

09:05.296 --> 09:07.298
You need to sniff
each other's butts, bare your teeth

09:07.423 --> 09:09.217
and arrive at some
strange dÃ©tente.

09:09.342 --> 09:11.636
Otherwise you'll
end up biting each other's eyes out.

09:11.761 --> 09:15.598
Again, with all the
love in the world.

09:17.725 --> 09:19.227
I'll let you sniff first.

09:19.477 --> 09:21.562
Take my deal or get
out of my apartment.

09:21.687 --> 09:25.650
Take my deal or I move in.

09:31.822 --> 09:34.700
This guy worked for Habitat
for Humanity in Costa Rica.

09:34.825 --> 09:36.619
And coaches handicapped kids.

09:36.744 --> 09:38.454
You think we should do a work up,
on the other coaches?

09:38.579 --> 09:40.206
It is possible
he's too perfect.

09:40.331 --> 09:42.458
I'm not saying he's perfect,
I'm saying he's trying to be.

09:42.583 --> 09:44.585
It's what people do.

09:46.212 --> 09:47.088
What?

09:47.213 --> 09:48.506
That's not what people do.

09:48.631 --> 09:52.218
People usually suck, but they
want to be good, want to be nice.

09:52.343 --> 09:53.678
House?

09:54.011 --> 09:55.763
Exception that
proves the rule.

09:56.138 --> 09:57.765
What sort of
argument is that?

09:57.890 --> 09:58.933
Bad one.

10:03.062 --> 10:04.981
That might be relevant.

10:05.606 --> 10:09.819
Hydrofluoric acid. Lowers his calcium,
causes the fainting and taste issue.

10:09.944 --> 10:12.029
But not the niceness.

10:12.154 --> 10:13.614
Wouldn't that be nice?

10:16.409 --> 10:18.577
You are King Solomon.

10:19.537 --> 10:21.872
If you want us to cut him in half,
we're cool with that.

10:21.998 --> 10:24.834
My boyfriend's too much of a wuss
to make the call for himself.

10:24.959 --> 10:27.336
And I mean that with
all the love in the world.

10:27.461 --> 10:30.923
I'm gonna piss off one of them.
And they both scare me.

10:47.815 --> 10:50.651
"Your treatment of patients
is reprehensible."

10:50.776 --> 10:51.902
You're reading his
performance review?

10:52.028 --> 10:54.530
I'm busy. We have
a nurses' strike.

10:54.655 --> 10:57.450
"Your management of employees
borders on abuse."

10:57.575 --> 10:59.160
Let's go.

10:59.452 --> 11:02.371
No, I...
I want to hear it.

11:02.496 --> 11:05.249
"You are overtly contemptuous
of hospital hierarchy."

11:05.374 --> 11:07.168
And covertly.

11:07.293 --> 11:10.004
But I suppose, you
didn't know about that.

11:10.129 --> 11:13.841
"Your attitude towards supervisory
personnel is disrespectful.

11:13.966 --> 11:17.178
"And a disturbingly large proportion of
your comments are racist or sexist."

11:17.303 --> 11:20.681
That top makes you look
like an Afghani prostitute.

11:21.015 --> 11:22.975
Would be an example of that.

11:23.100 --> 11:25.686
Sign this.

11:25.811 --> 11:27.855
- House, I got the...
- It can wait.

11:27.980 --> 11:30.191
I will sign if you
will give us a ruling.

11:30.316 --> 11:34.195
I will give you a ruling
if you do the reviews on your team.

11:37.239 --> 11:41.035
I'd be happy to continue
the mockery of this process.

11:41.827 --> 11:43.996
- What did you offer him?
- Wednesdays till 11 :00,

11:44.121 --> 11:45.039
and alternate weekends.

11:45.164 --> 11:47.875
Wednesdays till 11 :00,
and alternate weekends.

11:48.000 --> 11:51.837
Yes! Wednesday nights
are Ladies' Nights at Cheetah's.

11:52.963 --> 11:54.173
Calcium's normal.

11:54.298 --> 11:56.008
Wow. It really could wait.

11:56.133 --> 11:57.927
- Everything's normal.
- And you thought it wouldn't be?

11:58.052 --> 12:00.221
He's a carpet cleaner, he's got
a home full of hydrofluoric acid.

12:00.346 --> 12:01.931
Doesn't mean his
calcium should be low.

12:02.056 --> 12:04.392
Yeah, actually, it kind of does.
HF causes lower levels of...

12:04.517 --> 12:06.519
- Lower, not low.
- Lower than normal.

12:06.644 --> 12:08.354
Lower than yesterday.
Yesterday might have been high.

12:08.479 --> 12:10.356
What's lower than high?

12:11.565 --> 12:13.984
He actually has hypercalcemia,

12:14.110 --> 12:15.945
which is being lowered
to normal by the HF.

12:16.070 --> 12:18.614
So what gives us elevated calcium,
bad taste and fainting?

12:18.739 --> 12:20.032
I take it you know.

12:20.157 --> 12:22.326
Get the team.
This is gonna be fun.

12:26.747 --> 12:28.874
Hello, again.

12:28.999 --> 12:32.586
These people think
you're not too nice.

12:32.795 --> 12:34.713
Too nice? For what?

12:34.839 --> 12:37.800
For life as we know it to have evolved
without an intelligent designer.

12:37.925 --> 12:39.927
I'm going to
prove them wrong.

12:40.052 --> 12:42.096
Your wife is very ugly.

12:42.221 --> 12:43.097
Get out of here.

12:43.222 --> 12:44.140
JEFF: Deb...

12:45.349 --> 12:48.227
He's obviously
trying to prove a point.

12:49.103 --> 12:52.982
I think I just did. You're either
perfect or you're sick.

12:53.107 --> 12:54.942
And in my experience,
sick is much more common.

12:55.067 --> 12:56.777
He's not sick. He's nice.

12:56.902 --> 12:59.864
Nice in the sense that your toaster
is nice for making you breakfast.

12:59.989 --> 13:02.199
It's the only thing his
wiring will let him do.

13:02.324 --> 13:04.034
He has Williams Syndrome.

13:04.160 --> 13:07.621
Your husband is missing
the genes that make him suspicious.

13:07.746 --> 13:08.914
You're wrong, he's...

13:09.039 --> 13:10.916
Relax, there's no cure.

13:11.041 --> 13:13.210
He's gonna go right on
tasting lemon meringue pie,

13:13.335 --> 13:14.962
fainting and being a sap.

13:15.463 --> 13:16.964
What about the other symptoms?

13:17.089 --> 13:18.382
He has no other symptoms.

13:18.507 --> 13:19.633
But Williams does.

13:19.758 --> 13:21.760
He's got the teeth,
the glasses...

13:22.094 --> 13:23.721
Williams cuts IQ by 20...

13:23.846 --> 13:25.931
He doesn't work in
the physics department,

13:26.056 --> 13:28.100
except when they spill
a black hole on their carpet.

13:28.225 --> 13:30.019
Elfin appearance?

13:30.478 --> 13:33.606
Yeah, he's more Legolas
than Keebler.

13:33.731 --> 13:36.484
Bet you he can still crack
off a batch of Pecan Sandies.

13:36.609 --> 13:37.776
Perfect pitch?

13:38.068 --> 13:39.653
You love to karaoke, right?

13:40.779 --> 13:42.615
- I suck.
- Modest.

13:42.740 --> 13:45.075
- Another symptom.
- No, he really does suck.

13:45.743 --> 13:47.870
Give us a warble.
Know any Cher?

13:47.995 --> 13:50.206
No, but I know Bread.

13:51.290 --> 13:53.250
(SINGING)
<i>Baby,</i> I'm-a <i>want</i> you

13:54.168 --> 13:56.045
<i>Baby, I'm-a need you</i>

13:56.587 --> 14:01.425
<i>You're the only one
I care enough to hurt about</i>

14:01.550 --> 14:03.260
<i>Maybe I'm-a...</i>

14:04.094 --> 14:08.641
(SINGING INCOHERENTLY)

14:08.766 --> 14:09.767
What's the matter?

14:09.892 --> 14:10.809
(GROANS)

14:10.935 --> 14:12.686
He's stroking!

14:17.816 --> 14:19.860
Not a moment too soon.

14:30.913 --> 14:32.665
TAUB: You were wrong.

14:32.957 --> 14:36.877
Why do people say that with such
pleasure? It's very hurtful, you know.

14:37.002 --> 14:39.672
It means the patient gets to keep
being nice. Why does that offend you?

14:39.797 --> 14:40.923
It's the way he said it.

14:41.048 --> 14:45.678
He wasn't relieved, he was excited.
He was also wrong.

14:45.803 --> 14:47.805
And I say that with
no sense of pleasure.

14:47.930 --> 14:49.348
KUTNER: Patient tested
negative for Williams,

14:49.473 --> 14:51.559
which means the stroke
and everything else wasn't caused...

14:51.684 --> 14:55.688
You have a friendly demeanor
but you sometimes get too involved.

14:55.813 --> 14:58.566
You relate well
to your peers and patients

14:58.691 --> 15:01.735
and you complete tasks
in a timely manner.

15:02.152 --> 15:03.821
Please sign.

15:03.946 --> 15:05.239
- What the hell was that?
- I have to give

15:05.364 --> 15:07.449
each of you
performance reviews.

15:07.575 --> 15:10.536
Plenty of other conditions
can cause debilitating niceness.

15:10.661 --> 15:12.788
How is that supposed
to help him?

15:12.913 --> 15:15.249
I don't know,
how was it supposed to help Wilson?

15:15.374 --> 15:18.002
Cross out Wilson's name and the date
and then fill in your own.

15:18.127 --> 15:20.629
The point of a review
is to give feedback to help...

15:20.754 --> 15:22.548
I'm thinking neurosyphilis.

15:22.673 --> 15:25.551
Wouldn't show up on the MRI
without contrast.

15:27.636 --> 15:29.888
I'll go run the tests.

15:35.227 --> 15:39.273
He doesn't think it's syphilis, but
he's gonna go run those tests anyway.

15:39.398 --> 15:42.151
Because he doesn't know,
that's why we do tests.

15:42.276 --> 15:44.862
Because he's a wimp.
Because he's afraid of you.

15:44.987 --> 15:47.615
You want me to intimidate him
into not being afraid?

15:47.740 --> 15:49.783
- Not sure I know how to do that.
- Reviews make a difference.

15:50.034 --> 15:51.493
People have to listen,
so they have to learn...

15:51.619 --> 15:52.828
I don't think the right time

15:52.953 --> 15:55.914
to tell the dog not to pee
on the rug is semi-annually.

15:56.040 --> 15:57.833
You don't want to
do the paperwork.

15:57.958 --> 16:00.419
I am concerned
about the rain forest.

16:01.128 --> 16:02.171
(SIGHS)

16:02.296 --> 16:03.714
I'll do it.

16:03.839 --> 16:04.923
I know.

16:10.054 --> 16:11.972
I don't have syphilis.

16:12.097 --> 16:13.515
You don't know.

16:14.183 --> 16:16.143
How many ways
are there to get it?

16:16.268 --> 16:18.687
You can know who you had sex with,
you can't know who she...

16:18.812 --> 16:19.897
I do.

16:20.022 --> 16:21.273
Not for sure.

16:21.398 --> 16:26.987
It's a waste of time. I had a stroke.
You can't keep wasting time.

16:27.112 --> 16:28.280
We were tested
for the Peace Corps.

16:28.405 --> 16:29.698
Ten years ago.

16:29.823 --> 16:32.326
You haven't been with
your wife every minute of every day.

16:32.451 --> 16:34.536
You think I'm naive,
don't you?

16:34.662 --> 16:37.539
I think you're... Yeah.

