32:26.195 --> 32:28.489
I'm gonna be even more
attractive to the ladies.

32:28.615 --> 32:30.867
I was going to test for a heart issue
before the syphilis.

32:30.992 --> 32:32.410
PFO could explain
the heart attack,

32:32.535 --> 32:36.331
and reduced blood flow to the brain
could explain the rage.

32:36.456 --> 32:39.125
Well, they're all good ideas.

32:39.250 --> 32:40.501
Okay. Let's take a vote.

32:40.627 --> 32:43.379
How many think
it's the roids talking?

32:44.172 --> 32:46.507
And who's for the penicillin?

32:46.633 --> 32:49.636
And how about
whatever she said?

32:52.096 --> 32:54.515
Someone hasn't
raised their hand.

32:56.309 --> 32:58.394
Whatever I decide?

32:59.187 --> 33:00.938
You're setting me up.

33:01.064 --> 33:03.274
Why would I do that?

33:05.943 --> 33:07.403
PFO.

33:09.489 --> 33:10.823
'V : have it.

33:12.283 --> 33:16.287
I just hope the bubble test is positive.
Or it's no more Mr. Nice Guy.

33:23.211 --> 33:26.547
(CLATTERING)

33:26.673 --> 33:30.760
We gave van Gogh chelation therapy.
Turned him into a house painter.

33:31.177 --> 33:35.181
Maybe not.
Maybe we just put Hitler on Ritalin.

33:35.640 --> 33:37.600
Are you comparing
House to Hitler?

33:37.725 --> 33:38.768
Oh, God.

33:39.227 --> 33:42.230
Just because I don't think he's Hitler
doesn't mean I slept with him.

33:42.355 --> 33:45.525
I don't sleep with everyone
who's better than Hitler.

33:45.650 --> 33:49.404
Maybe Taub's right.
Maybe this is good.

33:49.529 --> 33:50.780
This is not good.

33:50.905 --> 33:55.535
He respected our opinions, he mocked
himself, he was civil, he shared.

33:55.827 --> 33:57.245
He didn't care.

33:57.370 --> 33:58.204
He never cares.

33:58.413 --> 34:02.083
He didn't vote. He always cared
about one thing,

34:02.208 --> 34:03.584
solving the puzzle.

34:03.710 --> 34:07.296
But he was irrelevant in that diagnosis,
he had no opinion of his own.

34:07.422 --> 34:10.883
He now cares about nothing.

34:11.008 --> 34:15.346
You had no choice, you had to treat him.
What's done is done.

34:24.355 --> 34:28.151
You know that thing I was going
to tell you? I gotta tell you.

34:28.693 --> 34:32.321
I gotta tell someone.
You have to swear not to tell C.B.

34:33.156 --> 34:35.408
- Whatever.
- That's not swearing, that's shrugging.

34:35.533 --> 34:37.452
It's actually the
opposite of swearing.

34:37.577 --> 34:39.203
I won't tell Amber.

34:45.334 --> 34:48.546
My team thinks
that I have syphilis.

34:49.338 --> 34:51.048
- Do you?
- Not yet.

34:51.799 --> 34:53.342
Why do they think you do?

34:53.468 --> 34:56.179
Because I knew they had access to
an old blood sample.

34:56.304 --> 34:58.431
I knew they'd test it
sometime for something.

34:58.556 --> 35:01.017
Why would you swap your blood?
What are you afraid they'll find?

35:01.142 --> 35:05.313
Shut up, you're missing the point.
Now they think that I'm on penicillin.

35:06.689 --> 35:09.525
Is this some clever practical
joke that I'm not aware of?

35:09.650 --> 35:13.070
And as I get better,
I get nicer.

35:18.451 --> 35:19.660
That's brilliant.

35:19.786 --> 35:22.413
Foreman thinks I actually
value his opinion.

35:22.538 --> 35:25.958
Thank God he said PFO
or I'd have had to do some dancing.

35:26.083 --> 35:27.293
You got time for bowling?

35:29.629 --> 35:32.340
Come on, it's work hours.

35:32.465 --> 35:34.675
I'll get my shoes.

35:36.761 --> 35:39.472
- So we don't need to talk about...
- No.

35:39.597 --> 35:41.098
- You're gonna keep screwing...
- Yeah.

35:41.724 --> 35:44.519
And you're gonna keep talking about it.
We are who we are.

35:46.062 --> 35:47.438
I'll get my shoes.

35:49.524 --> 35:53.069
Okay, got a good
view of the heart.

35:53.736 --> 35:59.158
What if we lower House's
dosage? Maybe stabilize him?

35:59.283 --> 36:01.410
He doesn't get worse,
he doesn't get better.

36:01.536 --> 36:04.664
Quite the line to walk. If we're wrong,
he dies of neurosyphilis.

36:04.789 --> 36:06.415
If we don't,
other people die.

36:06.541 --> 36:08.501
Other people
who aren't our boss.

36:08.626 --> 36:09.877
People.

36:10.503 --> 36:12.880
This sucks. The guy
had a gift. I killed...

36:15.216 --> 36:17.552
- Hi. What...
- House doesn't have syphilis.

36:17.677 --> 36:19.512
He switched
the blood samples.

36:20.304 --> 36:21.305
How do you know that?

36:21.430 --> 36:22.557
House told Wilson.

36:22.682 --> 36:25.518
I wanted to ruin
House's day. See you.

36:27.478 --> 36:29.480
- We're idiots.
- We're not idiots.

36:29.605 --> 36:31.274
Positive blood test
means positive blood test.

36:31.399 --> 36:32.692
Apparently not.

36:33.484 --> 36:35.486
There they are.
Let's see if they...

36:35.611 --> 36:37.738
What are you doing?
We're not done.

36:37.864 --> 36:39.490
He doesn't have syphilis.

36:40.241 --> 36:41.325
I know.

36:48.624 --> 36:51.919
KUTNER: Patient tested
positive for syphilis, right?

36:52.545 --> 36:53.921
Is this some sort of recap?

36:54.046 --> 36:56.632
But why did he test
positive for syphilis?

36:56.757 --> 36:58.759
Oh, oh, I know this.

36:58.968 --> 37:00.928
Either, one,
he has syphilis.

37:01.262 --> 37:02.138
I was gonna say that.

37:02.263 --> 37:04.265
Or two, the test
was wrong twice.

37:04.390 --> 37:07.768
Or three, he gave us
someone else's blood.

37:14.317 --> 37:16.277
- Who?
- Amber.

37:18.529 --> 37:22.617
Get that idiotic smile out of my face,
I gotta go on a killing spree.

37:22.909 --> 37:26.704
Or four, he has something that tests
positive for syphilis.

37:28.080 --> 37:29.790
- It's not Chagas.
- He worked in Costa Rica,

37:29.916 --> 37:30.958
before he was married.

37:31.334 --> 37:33.753
Is two a spree or do
I have to kill you too?

37:34.211 --> 37:35.838
Chagas wouldn't
explain the niceness.

37:35.963 --> 37:40.217
I've heard of remote tribes that
actually practice acts of kindness.

37:40.343 --> 37:42.970
Or the Chagas
caused encephalitis.

37:43.095 --> 37:44.221
The MRI showed no signs...

37:44.347 --> 37:47.099
Until we started him on steroids,
compromised the immune system

37:47.224 --> 37:48.517
and let the
infection flare up.

37:48.643 --> 37:52.188
I did another one.
It's not much.

37:55.191 --> 37:56.817
It's plenty.

37:58.736 --> 38:01.864
You figured this out
because I don't have syphilis?

38:03.616 --> 38:04.659
Damn.

38:06.285 --> 38:08.746
It should have
been my epiphany.

38:12.208 --> 38:14.043
Good news and bad news.

38:14.919 --> 38:17.880
Good news is,
we know what you have,

38:18.005 --> 38:21.717
it's treatable,
and you're going to live.

38:22.426 --> 38:24.136
Really?

38:24.261 --> 38:25.346
What's the bad news?

38:25.471 --> 38:28.849
The cure is a grueling
course of pills.

38:28.975 --> 38:30.059
It's like

38:30.184 --> 38:33.479
one a day for a month.

38:33.604 --> 38:35.648
Now you're just trying
to make me laugh.

38:35.773 --> 38:37.733
Yeah, like that's a challenge.

38:37.858 --> 38:39.360
You have Chagas disease.

38:39.485 --> 38:42.530
It's a parasite. It's been
asymptomatic for 10 years.

38:42.655 --> 38:45.741
Not quite. Your brain's been
swollen, not enough to see,

38:45.866 --> 38:47.410
but enough to alter
your personality.

38:47.535 --> 38:48.661
We're back to that?

38:48.786 --> 38:51.205
He screamed at you,
you don't think he can change?

38:51.330 --> 38:53.958
That was because of the drugs.

38:54.083 --> 38:57.294
So you think drugs
are more powerful than parasites?

38:57.420 --> 39:00.214
I mean, the ones we're gonna give you to
treat the parasites obviously are,

39:00.339 --> 39:03.843
but I stand by the principle.

39:03.968 --> 39:06.095
(JEFF BREATHES DEEPLY)

39:09.432 --> 39:11.767
I'm not worried.

39:11.892 --> 39:12.893
Neither am I.

39:15.104 --> 39:18.190
Neither am I. But that's
because I don't care.

39:34.123 --> 39:35.124
Reviews?

39:35.249 --> 39:37.960
It was brought to my
attention that, on occasion,

39:38.085 --> 39:40.212
I am not respectful
of hospital hierarchy.

39:40.337 --> 39:42.465
The word was "contemptuous."

39:49.138 --> 39:51.849
Well phrased, thoughtful...

39:54.935 --> 39:58.105
identically phrased.
These are all the same.

39:58.230 --> 40:02.651
Because underneath it all,
we are all the same.

40:02.777 --> 40:06.113
And Foreman refused
to type his up.

40:06.238 --> 40:07.531
Well, it's more
than I expected.

40:08.282 --> 40:10.242
There's an extra one in there.

40:20.211 --> 40:23.339
"Your treatment of patients
is nonexistent

40:23.464 --> 40:27.134
"because you're not a doctor,
you're an administrator."

40:27.259 --> 40:29.678
Foreman convinced me
that these could be helpful.

40:29.804 --> 40:31.722
"Your management
of employees is,

40:31.847 --> 40:35.142
well, let's face it, they're
outside carrying signs."

40:35.559 --> 40:38.979
The strike ended. The nurses have been
back for two shifts already.

40:39.105 --> 40:42.274
You'd think I'd have noticed.
What exactly did they do around here?

40:47.279 --> 40:52.618
"You act like employees should fear and
respect you, but your eyes tell us...

40:52.743 --> 40:55.621
"Actually your eyes tell us nothing,
because we're looking at your boobs,

40:55.746 --> 40:57.748
"which tell us that you're desperate
to have someone jump on you

40:57.873 --> 41:01.502
"and tell you they love you one grunted
syllable at a time.

41:01.627 --> 41:05.131
"What you want, you run away from.
What you need, you don't have a clue.

41:05.256 --> 41:09.510
"What you've accomplished
makes you proud.

41:09.635 --> 41:11.595
"But you're still miserable."

41:12.638 --> 41:14.390
Please sign.

41:16.892 --> 41:18.644
I got a call from Amber today.

41:18.769 --> 41:21.897
Says there's been
a violation your contract.

41:22.022 --> 41:24.817
You've been seeing
Wilson on her time.

41:24.942 --> 41:26.402
She breached confidentiality.

41:26.527 --> 41:29.655
You can let it slide,
Officer, we're even.

41:29.780 --> 41:33.159
Yes, you are.
You're both losing fingers.

41:36.537 --> 41:38.038
Look what I found.

41:38.164 --> 41:39.165
Nice.

41:42.835 --> 41:45.087
They think you might be able
to come home tomorrow.

41:45.212 --> 41:46.922
Yeah? That's good.

41:50.176 --> 41:51.218
What's the matter?

41:51.343 --> 41:54.680
The ketchup. There's something
wrong with that.

41:58.434 --> 42:01.228
Tastes fine.
ls there anything else?

42:01.353 --> 42:03.063
Everything else is great.

42:03.189 --> 42:07.443
I just, I don't know, I guess
I don't like ketchup anymore.

42:08.652 --> 42:10.905
Wonder what else I don't like.

42:29.089 --> 42:30.507
Roll over.

42:33.260 --> 42:35.012
We need a tougher punishment.

42:35.137 --> 42:37.890
You want to come over
to the poopy side?

42:39.225 --> 42:42.102
So where are you two
going Friday night?

42:42.228 --> 42:43.145
Dinner at L'Auberge.

42:46.941 --> 42:49.193
You're lying.

42:49.318 --> 42:50.277
Of course I am.
